edu.stanford.slac.aida.lib

Class ChannelProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • slac.aida.NativeChannelProvider
      • edu.stanford.slac.aida.lib.ChannelProvider
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AidaChannelProvider

    public abstract class ChannelProvider
extends NativeChannelProvider
    Implementation of a Channel Provider. A Channel Provider is responsible for communicating with the Native Channel Provider to get and receive information from the AIDA-PVA network.

    This class encodes generic functionality common to all Channel Providers on the AIDA-PVA network. Specific customisations should be coded in the AidaChannelProvider class.

    This class automatically calls the initialisation of the underlying Native Provider and shows the AIDA-PVA banner.

    It also handles the five main classes of requests routing them to the correct underlying - NativeChannelProvider entry point: - requestScalar(String, AidaArguments, AidaType) - requestScalarArray(String, AidaArguments, AidaType) - requestTable(String, AidaArguments) - setValue(String, AidaArguments) - setValueWithResponse(String, AidaArguments)

    • Constructor Detail

      • ChannelProvider

        public ChannelProvider()
        Constructor for the channel provider that reads the configuration from environment variables and configuration files.

        Uses ChannelProviderFactory.create(ChannelProvider) to check the `aida.pva.channels.filename` property or the `AIDA_PVA_CHANNELS_FILENAME` environment variable to load the yaml configuration file

        Lists the abbreviated list of hosted channels to the console.

        Calls the logHostedChannels()
